		<div class="servings">
			Change servings: 
			<input id="servings" type="number" min="0" step="1" value="1" onchange="changeservings(this.value);" />
		</div>
		<p>
			Endowed with the freedom that adulthood brings, I would be
			well within my rights to embark upon a gluttonous quest to find that perfect
			mint chocolate chip ice cream cake. 
			Thankfully, my vanity is what prevents me from doing so, and <span class="nm">Lila, Chop!</span> 
			inspired me to recreate my own mint chocolate chip ice cream
			experience in a guilt-free, clean, healthy and protein-rich maner.  
		</p>
		<table id="steps">
			<caption>Steps</caption>
			<thead>
				<tr>
					<th class="amount" colspan="2">time</th>
					<th>instruction</th>
				</tr>
			</thead>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount">1</td>
				<td class="unit">min</td>
				<td>blend all the ingredients in a high-speed blender until thick and creamy.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount">1</td>
				<td class="unit">min</td>
				<td>garnish with a fresh mint leaf and additional cacao nibs.</td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td class="amount"></td>
				<td class="unit"></td>
				<td>Serve cold and enjoy!</td>
			</tr>
		</table>
		<p>
			This is a very filling smoothie. To make the recipe leaner, simply use less avocado, and
			replace the frozen banana with crushed ice. Remember, the creamier
			the consistency and the more frozen the smoothie is, the more it will taste like ice cream. 	
		</p>
